
(1) Install the Node.js JavaScript runtime environment using your OS package manager.

    (On Ubuntu 18.04, just do 'apt-get install nodejs' as 'root', otherwise go to: https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager)


(2) Verify that Node.js has been installed:

    $ node -v

    v8.10.0


(3) Install the NPM Node Package Manager.

    (On Ubuntu 18.04, just do 'apt-get install npm' as 'root', otherwise go to: https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/installing-node#installing-npm-from-the-nodejs-site)


(4) Verify that NPM has been installed:

    $ npm -v

    3.5.2


(5) Install the version 3 of the Webpack module bundler:

    $ npm install webpack@webpack-3

    ...


(6) Install the Babel transpiler 'core' and 'loader':

    $ npm install babel-core babel-loader

    ...


(7) Install the Babel preset 'env':

    $ npm install babel-preset-env

    ...


(8) Install the Babel preset 'react':

    $ npm install babel-preset-react

    ...


(9) Install the NPM module for React:

    $ npm install react

    ...


(10) Install the NPM module for React DOM:

    $ npm install react-dom

    ...


(11) Bundle / transpile the JavaScript with Webpack for deployment:

    $ ./node_modules/webpack/bin/webpack.js -p --config ./webpack.config.js

    ...
